casebody.data:
Third Department,

September, 1945.

(September 12, 1945.) In the Matter of Abraham Levitt, Petitioner, against The Board of Regents of the University of the State of New York, Respondent.

Motion for reargument denied. Motion for leave to appeal to the Court of Appeals denied, without costs. Stay continued until the opening of the next session of the Court of Appeals in October, 1945. All concur. [See ante, p. 889.]
